y of Salamanca is around 90km northeast, with its international airport a further 20km. The local Hurdas region is famed for its landscape, character and authenticity. The natural beauty and traditional Iberian villages help to provide an incomparable experience for all visitors. The hotel itself is a carefully converted period stone and slate building dating back to the beginning of the 20th-century, surrounded by valleys and streams. Onsite facilities include an outdoor swimming pool, plus there is free Wi-Fi internet access throughout the premises for convenience. Alfonso XIII Restaurant offers a personal atmosphere and stunning views of the Hurdes landscape. The cuisine offered combines tradition and innovation, using local ingredients to create sophisticated dishes. Standard guestrooms are spacious and comfortably furnished, with magnificent views over the garden or the hills. They feature wooden floors and are decorated with soft lines and colours. Amenities include a flat-screen TV, personal computer and fully-equipped bathroom. Free public parking is possible onsite.</Text></Description><Amenity><Code>Safe</Code><Text>Safe</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>HandicapAccessible</Code><Text>Handicap accessible</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>TVInRoom</Code><Text>TV in room</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>OutdoorPool</Code><Text>Outdoor swimming pool</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>AirConditioning</Code><Text>Air conditioning</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>RoomService</Code><Text>Room service</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>HairDryer</Code><Text>Hair dryer</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>Bar</Code><Text>Bar</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>LaundryService</Code><Text>Laundry service</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>CarPark</Code><Text>Car parking</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>ReceptionArea</Code><Text>Reception Area</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>CheckIn24hr</Code><Text>24hr. CheckIn</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>Reception24hr</Code><Text>24hr. Reception</Text></Amenity><Am